<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>LAFORGE:  Hannah, my visor's positronic scan would have detected the leak. Its molecular pattern enhancer would have picked up even the smallest crack.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>HANNAH:  The damn thing doesn't miss much, does it. Fine. I'll tell them the truth. Will that make you happy?</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>LAFORGE:  Why are you doing this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>HANNAH:  I was born to be one of the best scientific minds of my generation, and in the past five days I have encountered technology that I have barely imagined. And I've got to ask myself, If we're so brilliant how come we didn't invent any of these things?</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>LAFORGE:  Well, maybe necessity really is the mother of invention. You never really look for something until you need it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>HANNAH:  But all my needs have been anticipated and planned for before I'm even born. All of us in this colony have been living in the dark ages. It's like we're victims of a two hundred year old joke. Until you came, we could only see to the wall of our biosphere. Suddenly our eyes have been opened to the infinite possibilities.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Observation lounge</td></tr>
<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>PICARD:  Asylum?</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>LAFORGE:  She wants to leave the colony.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>RIKER:  She may not be the only one. The science teams that went down to the surface fielded a lot of questions from colonists who were more than curious about what's outside their world.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>WORF:  Why shouldn't we grant them asylum?</td></tr>

